Our bill restores USPS operations & puts protections in place to make sure these services are available to the American people.

It means connecting a grandparent with their family.

It means helping local businesses ship the masks they’re sewing for first responders.

It means ensuring veterans receive the medication they need.

Severe weather can come at any time. The best defense is for families to create an emergency plan, practice that plan, and always stay alert and ready.

I’m glad to be part of a new PSA initiative with The @WeatherChannel to help each household prepare for the unexpected. https://t.co/agcUnqluuC

full_text:
Since I was a little girl, I was raised to fight for the rights of all people to be equal in the eyes of the law.

I am proud that we recently celebrated 5 years of marriage equality. We all must continue the hard work of ending discrimination in all of its forms. #HappyPride

I wear orange for all the families and victims across our country who have suffered from unnecessary gun violence.

I'm fighting alongside all of you to make sure everyone in America is safe. #GunViolenceAwarenessDay #WearOrange https://t.co/JNop9hzYTi

https://t.co/PJFrxK62Ks https://t.co/YtRJTziaXO

A mother’s love is never ending. Today, we honor the strength & protection a mother provides.

To all the Moms who lift us up & give us life — we celebrate you. I hope you all have a day filled with love & family.

#HappyMothersDay https://t.co/Su1mabLOLt

They faced violence and hardship. We honor their enduring legacy and that of my friend @repjohnlewis, whose bravery and perseverance continues to lead us toward justice.

- The IRS will not ask for the money back. https://t.co/aMBYd9Pakb

For too many mothers in America, the miracle of pregnancy ends in tragedy. That’s why we acted & introduced a historic package of bills to #SaveMoms. https://t.co/4TGrRFPR1M

To help keep people safe & healthy during the COVID-19 outbreak, I've co-sponsored:

• Paid sick days for low-wage workers
• No-cost coronavirus testing
• Plans to ensure kids continue receiving affordable meals if their schools close

For resources, visit my website. https://t.co/F1YteNmKHj

It's time to put aside differences & save American lives.

Because I know the pain of losing a child to gun violence.

I lost my son, but I am still his mother, and I’m on a mission to protect the lives of children like him.

How could God allow this to happen to me, to my family, to my Jordan.

So, I prayed. I prayed and I prayed and I prayed

And that is when my advocacy began.

full_text:
It was seven years ago, today.

Seven years ago my phone rang, and I knew.

I knew deep in my soul that my life would never be the same.

Seven years ago, today, my son Jordan; my beautiful, smart, caring boy, was shot and killed by a man with hate in his heart.

Over 252,000 women are diagnosed with breast cancer each year in the United States.

As a two-time breast cancer survivor, I know firsthand that early detection is the key to catching cancer. Please be sure to schedule your annual screening! #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth https://t.co/H9QGms9BiE

Week after week, day after day, innocent Americans are being murdered driving to work, shopping for clothes, and enjoying their weekends.

How much more death until we all demand change.

Inaction is unacceptable. We MUST do something.

full_text:
Proud to introduce this legislation with my colleagues.

No mom-to-be should be forced out of a job or denied employment opportunities because she is pregnant.

#VAWA19 https://t.co/rNFxCRWEmu

It is one thing to get a student to college. It is another to get them through college.
 
I’m excited that today's bipartisan hearing in @EdLaborCmte regarding higher education was the first of many.
 
I look forward to continuing these conversations.
 
#TheValueofCollege https://t.co/sFgVInE55c

In @HouseJudiciary we are still marking up #HR8 so that we can bring this historic gun violence prevention legislation to the floor of the House.

@MomsDemand volunteers have been here since 10am.

Their commitment to #EndGunViolence is inspiring. https://t.co/3edbF4bci8
